replies.bodyText:
We can swing the params down onto a new line.
My personal style is to indent +8 off the method block, which differentiates it from the method body, and the method signature.
@NonNull
<T extends Model> GraphQLResponse<ModelWithMetadata<T>> delete(
        @NonNull Class<T> clazz,
        @NonNull String objectId,
        @NonNull Integer version,
        @Nullable QueryPredicate predicate)
        throws DataStoreException {
    doStuffHereAtPlus4();
    coolStuffOnly();
    thatIs();
}

The rule is basically "Chomp down vars in a method signature, and indent by 8."
I know of no tool that is able to uniquely distinguish this case, from other line-wrapping or indentation cases.
My personal style is to use +4 spaces as indentation in all other situations in a Java document.
Well,
final class MyClass implements
        SameTypeOfThing,
        Here {
    public void soThatYouCanTellItIsntThisMethodEasily() {
    }
}

