Daniel and I agree we should just pass down the predicate, here. Even if it just means predicate != null is checked as a method-local implementation detail.
Alternately, I am always tryign to get people to do:
enum LabeledBoolean {
    STATE_A,
    STATE_B
}

with
exerciseBehavior(LabeledBoolean.STATE_A);

It's a more legible experience to read that, than exerciseBeahvior(false) -- the false is meaningless until I read the code.

